GROUP MEMBER: Yufan Fei, Yufei Gao  

**pre.JPG**  
This is my wireframes before crits. My design philosophy is  
to keep everything as clean as possible. The original cafe wegpage  
is somewhat lengthy such that one need to scroll all the way down  
till a specific location to find what he may need. This is inconvenience  
in practice. Therefore, instead of using a static webpage, I decide to  
create a map of those restaurants with their current status at the center of the webpage.  
 Once the user click on any of the restaurant, They can then look into the menu  
and operating hours of their choice.

**final.JPG**
After receiving crits, I realize that though the idea is good. The layout  
of the pre design is not enough to list that much of information at the same time.  
Therefore, Instead of showing everthing in the same page, I decide to split to restaurant-specific  
information into a pop-up modal. There would be serveral tabs available from the users to choose from  
such that all things are concatenated in one page without the need to scroll up/down.
